Theory 

Explanation: The paper discusses the theoretical issue of overfitting in the context of selecting a hypothesis from a set of hypotheses using cross-validation data. It proposes a new algorithm based on leave-one-out cross-validation to address this issue. While the paper mentions the use of a randomized learning algorithm to generate the set of hypotheses, it does not focus on any specific sub-category of AI such as neural networks or genetic algorithms.
